<h3 id="how-to-set-it-up">How to set it up</h3>

<p>There are two main steps.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Connecting the mic to your phone</li>
  <li>Enabling OTG to make it work</li>
</ol>

<p>First, connect the micâ€™s USB cable to the OTG cable, and then connect it to your phone. If your mic switches on, then you can be sure that its connected. On the Snowball, the red indicator light switches on when I connect it to my phone.</p>

<p>Next, you need to enable OTG on your phone. Go to Settings -&gt; Storage &amp; memory -&gt; Enable OTG storage.</p>

<p>Thatâ€™s it! Now, open Sing!, and try to record audio. If youâ€™re able to save the recording, then youâ€™re good to go.</p>
